{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fda5597c-76ae-49a3-bd0f-f1c4e7c75d9e","content":"### 3. Create the GitHub environment\n\nIn your repo settings at **Settings → Environments**, create an environment named **`nuget`**. Optionally add protection rules (e.g., require approval).\n\n---\n\n**How it works:** The workflow uses `id-token: write` permission so the runner gets an OIDC token. NuGet.org validates that token against your trusted publisher registration — no API key needed. The `dotnet nuget push` command without `--api-key` will automatically use the OIDC token when the trusted publisher matches.\n\n**To publish:** push a tag like `git tag v1.0.0 && git push --tags`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5a1f9693-4cd1-490f-8c70-eab2f61edad9","outputTokens":150,"requestId":"0405:1CDC41:47875A:53548F:69F00513"},"id":"f5aa1479-58b6-4fad-8e24-82ca03c65a7b","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:53:45.993Z","parentId":"ba2b1447-5519-47de-be4f-a8aa10acf4cc"}
